snippet.title: Who Will Thank You in Heaven?
snippet.description:
Today’s message, filled with hope and reflection, dives deep into our collective vision of heaven and the vital role we play in sharing our faith. Whether you're new here or a longtime member, we’re so glad you’ve joined us.

Message Highlights:

Envisioning Heaven: What does the Bible say about heaven? How does it compare to our personal hopes and dreams?

Gratitude: The importance of thanking those who led us to Christ.

Your Role in Heaven: Reflect on who will be in heaven because of you. Have you shared the gospel and invited others to join you on this spiritual journey?

Practical Evangelism: Learn how to create a list of people you want to share your faith with and practical steps on how to engage with them.

Scriptural Guidance: Insights from 2 Corinthians 5 and Luke 14 on viewing others through the lens of their need for salvation.

We hope this message inspires and equips you to actively participate in God’s mission. Together, let's make a difference and fill heaven with those we love.

snippet.title: Facing Your Fears: How to Share Your Faith with Confidence
snippet.description:
Have you ever felt scared or nervous about sharing your faith with others? You’re not alone! In this video, we talk about why sharing our faith can be tough and how we can make it easier. Learn how asking good questions, sharing your story, and trusting God can help you talk about Jesus with friends and family. 

Join us as we explore three important principles to help you share your faith with confidence and love.

snippet.title: Evangelism: Why Everyone Needs to Know
snippet.description:
This weekend, we're also kicking off an exciting new three-week sermon series called "Speak Easy." Despite the name, it’s not about prohibition-era drinks! Instead, we're diving into the topic of evangelism – a word that sometimes carries a bit of baggage. Over the next three weeks, we’ll explore why evangelism is so important and how we can share our faith in a loving, relationship-focused way.

Today, we'll start with the "why" of evangelism, followed by practical "how-to" steps in the coming weeks. Our goal is to empower and equip you to share the hope we have in Jesus Christ, especially as we approach the fall season and new routines begin.

Join us as we delve into the Great Commandment (Mark 12) and the Great Commission (Matthew 28) to understand our mission to love our neighbors and preach the gospel. Let’s embrace our role in spreading the good news and being good neighbors in our daily lives.

Thank you for being a part of our community. Let's go out and make a difference together!

snippet.title: Does God Expect Us To Be Perfect?
snippet.description:
While striving for perfection may seem daunting, we're reminded that with God, all things are possible. The journey towards being perfected in love is about relying on God's grace and the transformative power of the Holy Spirit. As we press on towards the goal, leaving behind past failures, we are encouraged to strive for greatness in our faith.

Join us as we learn to embrace God's high expectations, lean into His grace, and be inspired to live out our faith with excellence. Whether you're here for the sermon, seeking community, or simply finding solace, we're glad you're with us. Let's grow together in Christ's love.

snippet.title: Finding Faith and Resilience Amidst Life's Storms
snippet.description:
Today’s message, "Finding Faith and Resilience Amidst Life's Storms," touches on the unpredictability of life and the strength we find in faith.

 Despite the chaos brought by Hurricane Beryl, the message is clear: God's love remains steadfast, regardless of our circumstances. Whether you have power or are still in the dark, whether you’ve faced minor inconveniences or significant hardships, know that Jesus loves you.

We also explore the importance of avoiding bad theology in times of crisis. Our pastor warns against interpreting individual events as signs of divine favor or disfavor. Instead, we are reminded that we live in a broken world in need of redemption, and it’s through Jesus Christ that we find restoration and hope.

Lastly, the message calls us to examine our discipleship and the cost of following Jesus. True faith requires commitment, sacrifice, and a willingness to endure hardships. But the rewards of a life fully devoted to Christ are beyond measure.

As we navigate through these challenging times, let us be a church that supports and uplifts each other. If you need help, please reach out – you are not alone. We are here to serve and stand by you.

snippet.title: What to do When You Reach Your Breaking Point
snippet.description:
Today's message dives deep into a relatable and profound topic: reaching our breaking point. We all have moments where stress, fatigue, and frustration culminate in anger. Whether it's traffic woes, work pressures, or family challenges, these instances test our patience and resilience. In this message, we reflect on these moments and find wisdom in the story of Jesus reaching His own breaking point. We explore the powerful narrative of Jesus flipping the tables in the temple, an event recorded in all four Gospels. What made Jesus angry? How can we ensure our actions do not evoke such anger from Him?

Through the lens of Matthew 21, we examine the implications of Jesus' actions and uncover the deeper lessons about justice, compassion, and maintaining the purity of our spiritual temple. Join us as we navigate our emotions and align our lives more closely with the teachings of Christ.

snippet.title: How can we avoid falling into temptations?
snippet.description:
Drawing from Matthew 18:6-9, we're exploring how temptations, both internal and external, can lead us away from our path with God. Jesus’ teachings remind us of the serious consequences of sin and the importance of cutting off anything that causes us to stumble.

This message is part of our ongoing sermon series "Believe It or Not," where we dive into the challenging truths Jesus shared. Today’s sermon also emphasizes the protection and care we should have for the vulnerable, especially children, both in age and faith.

Join us as we reflect on our spiritual walk, seek to remove the stumbling blocks in our lives, and embrace the love and forgiveness that Jesus offers. Whether you’re here for the first time or a long-time member, we pray this message encourages and strengthens your faith.

snippet.title: Facing Our Demons: The Power of Jesus to Set Us Free
snippet.description:
In today’s message, we explore a powerful story from the Bible about Jesus and a man who was possessed by demons. We look at the battle between good and evil. We’ll talk about how the movie “The Exorcist” influenced people‘s thoughts on possession, and hear about a real-life exorcism that left doctors amazed.

We’ll dive into the gospel of Mark to learn about Jesus’ incredible power to free people from their struggles. This story shows us that Jesus cares about every one of us, no matter what we’re going through. 

Join us as we discover how Jesus’ love and grace can bring freedom and hope to our lives. Don’t forget to like, subscribe, and share this message with your friends!

snippet.title: Spiritual Growth Requires Patience
snippet.description: In our spiritual journey, we often seek clarity, yet true understanding unfolds over time. The story of Jesus healing a blind man in two stages in Mark 8:22-26 illustrates the gradual process of spiritual enlightenment. Initially, the man sees people as trees walking, but with Jesus's second touch, his sight is fully restored. This teaches us that spiritual growth requires patience and that life's messiness can lead to a deeper faith. This message will guide you through the importance of patience, trust in God's timing, and the call to consecration in our spiritual growth. If you're seeking answers on how to navigate your faith journey, find inspiration here to move from uncertainty to a place of clear vision and purpose. Join us in reflecting on this transformative biblical narrative and its application to our lives today.

snippet.title: Embrace Your Unique Spiritual Gifts
snippet.description: Ever wondered how your unique talents can serve a higher purpose? Discover how the Holy Spirit's gifts can transform your life and the lives of those around you. We'll explore the significance, variety and purpose of the Holy Spirit's gifts, such as wisdom, knowledge, and healing, emphasizing their role in edifying the church and glorifying God. We'll also address the theological debate on the continuation of these gifts and encourage you to pray for, use, and recognize these gifts in others to transform the church and the world.

snippet.title: How to Live a Life Led by the Spirit
snippet.description: Ever felt the Holy Spirit nudging you towards something greater or wondered how you can live a life led by the Spirit?  Discover how the Holy Spirit, a coequal member of the Trinity, functions as an advocate, counselor, helper, and comforter in our lives. Learn about the significance of being 'born of water and the Spirit' as described by Jesus, and understand the transformative power of the Holy Spirit's indwelling presence. This video dives into the importance of surrendering to the Holy Spirit's guidance and how it can lead to a life of love, service, and sacrifice. If you're seeking spiritual growth, guidance, comfort, or wisdom, this video provides insights into how the Holy Spirit can impact your daily decisions and actions. Join us in exploring the profound relationship between believers and the Holy Spirit, and how to live a life led by the Spirit.

snippet.title: Who is the Holy Spirit?
snippet.description: Who is the Holy Spirit, and how does He influence our lives as Christians? Learn about the fruit of the Spirit as evidence of His work within us and the importance of remaining connected to Jesus to cultivate these characteristics. Understand the necessity of crucifying our desires to live by the Spirit. If you're seeking spiritual growth, guidance on walking with the Spirit, or insights into Christian theology, this sermon will provide you with the answers. Don't forget to subscribe for more biblical teachings and share this video to help spread the word of God's transformative power through the Holy Spirit.

snippet.description:
Join us in celebrating Pentecost Sunday with our latest message where we'll answer the question, 'What is Pentecost?' Discover the profound meaning behind this pivotal day when the Holy Spirit descended upon the apostles, uniting believers and marking the beginning of the Christian church. Don't miss out on the opportunity to reflect on your spiritual influence and consider ways to engage in discipleship and mentoring within your community. snippet.title: Does the Bible Say, Love the Sinner, Hate the Sin?
snippet.description:
Have you ever heard the phrase, "Love the Sinner, Hate the Sin"? Discover the truth behind the Christian call to love others in this inspiring message. While the phrase "love the sinner, hate the sin" is commonly cited, we look at its origins and biblical accuracy. This video offers insights into showing compassion, celebrating progress in faith, and understanding God's unconditional love for us. Instead, learn how the Bible portrays the heart as deceitful and in need of God's leadership. Find out how to guard your heart against sin and deception and guide it towards eternal treasures. This message is a must-watch for anyone seeking to align their desires with God's purpose. snippet.description:

snippet.title: The Biblical Practice of Meditation
snippet.description: Explore the transformative power of biblical meditation in this enlightening message. Discover how meditation is not just an Eastern practice but a biblical one that can deepen your faith and bring you closer to God. Learn the three key principles for effective biblical meditation: steeping yourself in Scripture, embracing silence, and seeking solitude. This video is perfect for those seeking spiritual growth, stress relief, and a deeper understanding of God's word. Join us for a guided meditation on the Gospel of John and prepare your heart for Holy Week. Don't forget to like, subscribe, and share this video with others who might find solace in biblical meditation.

snippet.title: The Life-Changing Power of Sabbath
snippet.description:
Today we're exploring the life-changing power of the Sabbath. We'll learn how just 24 hours of rest can transform your relationship with God and bring peace to your soul. Learn the biblical significance of the Sabbath, how Jesus redefined it, and gain practical tips for observing this holy day in your own life. Whether you're seeking spiritual renewal or a break from the hectic pace of modern life, this message offers guidance on how to pick a day for rest, praise God, pause from work, and play to enjoy His creation. Be sure to subscribe to our channel for more inspiring messages to encourage you to find rest in God's rhythm of life.
 
#sabbath #RestInGod #SpiritualRenewal #BiblicalTeaching #ChurchSermon #ChristianLife #FindRest #ChangeYourRhythm #EmbraceSabbath #EnjoyLife

snippet.title: Transformative Spiritual Practices | Adoration
snippet.description: As we continue talking about transformative spiritual practices and daily rhythms that draw us closer to God, we're exploring the profound practice of adoration. Adoration has the power to reshape our prayer lives and deepen our connection with God. Join us as we unpack the essence of adoration, reflecting on its impact on our understanding of God's character, its ability to shift our focus from self to the divine, and its role in fostering confession and intimacy with God. Discover how incorporating adoration into your daily routine can lead to a life filled with awe, gratitude, and closeness to God. We'll also share some practical tips and insights for incorporating adoration into your spiritual journey.

snippet.title: Overcoming Lies About Prayer
snippet.description:
If you've ever felt inadequate in your prayer life or struggled to connect with God, you're not alone. Today, we're candidly sharing about our own challenges with prayer and dismantling common misconceptions surrounding it.

Throughout the message, we tackle three prevalent lies about prayer. Firstly, the misconception that prayer is only for the super-righteous or holy individuals. Secondly, the belief that unanswered prayers indicate prayer's ineffectiveness. And finally, the notion that prayer must be elaborate or verbose to be powerful.

Drawing from real-life examples, biblical teachings, and personal anecdotes, we uncover the power of simple prayers and the transformative impact they can have on our lives. Whether you're a seasoned prayer warrior or just beginning your journey of faith, this episode offers practical insights and encouragement to revitalize your prayer life.

snippet.title: Instruction Manual for Life
snippet.description:
In this engaging message, we'll discuss the significance of embracing life's instruction manual (The Bible), and why understanding and applying this instruction manual to our lives matters. Discover practical steps to dive into the study of scripture, debunking common misconceptions and fears associated with the word "study." Learn how making a plan, choosing the right translation, and developing a systematic approach can transform your engagement with the Bible.

With a blend of humor, relatability, and wisdom, this message will encourage you to embrace the Bible as life's ultimate instruction manual. Whether you're seeking guidance, inspiration, or simply curious about how to enrich your spiritual journey, this video will give you insights and practical tips to help you navigate life's challenges with confidence and purpose.

snippet.title: Rhythms of Life: Finding Spiritual Discipline in Chaos
snippet.description: Join us as we as we dive into the intricacies of life's rhythms and the spiritual disciplines that guide us through even the most chaotic seasons. Discover the countercultural practices of Lent and fasting, as we look at their relevance in today's fast-paced world. Learn more about biblical teachings on fasting, and how denying oneself can lead to profound spiritual encounters. Throughout this journey, we'll provide practical tips and encouragement to embrace spiritual rhythms, regardless of life's season. Hope you'll join us!

snippet.title: Called: Luann's Story
snippet.description: Today we're diving into the meaning of being called, understanding your primary calling as a believer, and uncovering your unique secondary calling in the world. Join us as we share personal stories of surrender, transformation, and finding purpose in our journey towards pastoral ministry. Gain insights into navigating seasons of doubt, embracing unexpected paths, and experiencing the transformative power of God's call in our lives. Whether you're seeking guidance on discerning your calling or simply curious about the experiences that shape our faith, this message offers hope, relatable struggles, and inspiring moments of divine intervention. Tune in and embark on a journey of self-discovery, faith exploration, and embracing the call to follow Jesus in every aspect of life.

snippet.title: How is God Calling Me?
snippet.description: Today we're exploring the question that resonates with many of us "How is God calling me?" Join us as we share personal stories that go beyond the traditional sermon format. Why share our stories? It's not about us; it's about the greater narrative of God's love and purpose for your life. So, how do you find your call? It's not about fitting a predetermined mold. It's about discovering where your passion aligns with the needs of the world. Whether it's in your career, parenting, volunteering, or mentoring, God is calling you to make a difference.

snippet.title: Transformative Lessons from the Early Church
snippet.description: Today we're diving into the transformative lessons from the early church in Acts 2:42, exploring the keys to a thriving church and spiritual growth. Join us as we uncover the characteristics that fueled the explosive growth of the early church and learn how to apply them in today's context. Discover the importance of being devoted to God's word, fostering genuine fellowship, and living a shared life that leads to daily worship and prayer. Whether you're a seasoned believer or new to the faith, these timeless principles are sure to inspire and guide you on your spiritual journey. Don't miss out on the fullness of life that God has for you – hit subscribe and let's explore the path to a flourishing and devoted church together!

snippet.title: The Transformative Power of Gratitude
snippet.description: Explore the transformative power of gratitude as we delve into Luke 17 and discover the importance of living a life marked by thankfulness. Join us in this insightful sermon, where we discuss the goals we set in various aspects of life and emphasize the ultimate goal of hearing 'well done, my good and faithful servant' from Jesus. Learn how gratitude not only connects us with God but also positively impacts our mental and emotional well-being. Discover practical ways to cultivate a heart of gratitude and why it's key to becoming a church that is truly grateful. Don't miss this inspiring message on building a life worthy of God's commendation.

snippet.title: Life's Unexpected Challenges
snippet.description: Join us for an exhilarating journey as we explore the parallels between a thrilling whitewater rafting trip and life's unexpected challenges. In this engaging sermon we'll discover how being guided by scripture can help you navigate the rapids of health, relationships, and more. Understand the transformative power of God's Word in shaping our lives as we explore faith, purpose, and the promises of God in the midst of life's turbulent waters.

snippet.title: The Gospel of Jesus Christ is Generous
snippet.description: The Gospel of Jesus Christ is generous. Join us as we examine how this generosity shapes our lives and inspires us to respond to the boundless love of God. We'll look into the scriptures that illuminate the true motivation for God's generosity, rooted in love, and gain insights into the profound meaning behind God's generous gift of Jesus Christ and how it extends to the abundance and beauty of the world around us. Discover the difference between being a believer and a disciple, and be inspired to embark on a journey of growth in faith. Whether you're considering saying yes to Jesus or moving from belief to discipleship, find guidance on responding to the generosity of God in Christ Jesus.

snippet.title: Navigating Life's Challenges: Managing Our Expectations in Faith
snippet.description: Navigating life's challenges and our expectations for how we think life "should" be isn't easy. In this message, we're looking at the impact of expectations in relationships and faith, drawing insights from a heartfelt discussion on difficult conversations, job surprises, and relationship shifts. Discover the power of voicing expectations and how they can shape the reality of our lives. Join us as we explore the importance of true expectations in faith and how they differ from false ones that may lead to disappointment. Learn to embrace the journey, trusting that God's expectations for us are rooted in love, peace, and joy.

snippet.title: What is True Love?
snippet.description: What is true love? In this message, Pastor Daniel leads us through a thought-provoking exploration of what true love really means and how it goes beyond mere feelings. Pastor Daniel challenges the common misconception that love is solely a feeling and reveals how the Christian faith provides a unique perspective on love. Discover the biblical definition of love, rooted in the concept of agape – a selfless, sacrificial love that mirrors God's love for us. Learn why love is not just a sentiment but a choice, a pursuit, and a commitment. Gain insights into the profound nature of God's love and understand why receiving His love is crucial for a fulfilled life.

snippet.title: Finding Peace in the Story of Christmas
snippet.description: Peace – it's a longing that echoes through the ages. In this message, we'll talk about how the biblical perspective on peace differs from the world's definitions, and learn more about the Hebrew concept of Shalom. Understand how Jesus, the Prince of Peace, brings completeness and restoration to our past, present, and future, and walk with us through the profound words of Isaiah, exploring the promise of a child born to bring everlasting peace. Discover how the Holy Spirit provides a supernatural peace, transcending our reality and transforming our daily lives.

snippet.title: How to Find Joy in Unexpected Places
snippet.description: Today we're talking about finding joy in unexpected places. Join us as we explore the true meaning of joy and how, like the shepherds in Luke Chapter 2, we can discover lasting joy even in unexpected circumstances. If you've ever found yourself wondering how you can hold on to joy in midst of difficult times, this message is for you.

snippet.title: The Gift of Hope - Advent
snippet.description:
The Christmas season is upon us. Lights, trees, presents, parties and stress abound. It’s so easy to get caught up in the busyness of this season that we can miss the beauty of it all. That’s why this Advent, we’re seeking to recapture the childlike wonder of Christmas. For children, this season is
marked by presents wrapped under the tree, and over the next four weeks, we’ll see how Jesus’ birth is a gift to our weary world. Because God put on flesh and was born in a manger in Bethlehem, we receive the gifts of hope, joy, peace and love. Whether this season is filled with wonder or filled with weariness for you, we’re glad that you’ve joined us at Loft!

snippet.title: Navigating Faith in a Digital World
snippet.description: How do we navigate faith in an increasingly digital world? In today's message, we're looking at the dynamic relationship between faith and technology. We'll share two practical principles to navigate the relationship between faith and technology and help you learn why being aware of technology's influence and regularly evaluating your relationship with it are crucial for maintaining a healthy balance. If you're curious about the impact of technology on our lives and how it aligns with our Christian beliefs this message is for you!

snippet.title: Navigating Faith and Politics
snippet.description:
In this message titled "Navigating Faith and Politics," we dive into the intersection of our faith and the political realm. Join us as we explore the philosophical and practical aspects of this crucial topic. Whether you're excited, uncomfortable, or curious, we're here to tackle the taboo and see what happens!

📖 In this message, we discuss the inherent political nature of our faith, rooted in the declaration "Jesus is Lord." Discover why faith and politics are intertwined and how we, as Christians, can engage biblically in the political arena.

🤔 We'll share a 30,000-foot view of the philosophical perspective of faith and politics, followed by three practical ways Christians can engage politically according to the Bible.

🌐 Remember, our hope is not in government or politicians but in Jesus, who is our ultimate Lord. Let's explore together how to navigate the balance between faith and politics without making politics our religion.

🙏 If you're new to Loft, we don't shy away from challenging conversations. Subscribe for more thought-provoking discussions on faith and life!

#faithandpolitics #churchandpolitics #christianpolitics

snippet.title: Faith and Work: Cody Nath
snippet.description:
Hey there, Loft community! Get ready for an uplifting and relatable message from Cody Nath, a member of our church family, as he shares his insights on faith and work.

🔥 Learn about the theology of work
🔥 Discover the power of faith in your workplace
🔥 Find inspiration to make a positive impact
🔥 Connect faith and work in a meaningful way

Watch Cody's message and be prepared to view your job in a whole new light. Let's dive in!

snippet.title: Can Christians Enjoy Secular Entertainment?
snippet.description:
Can Christians enjoy secular entertainment, or should they avoid it entirely? In this video, we dive into Acts chapter 17 to see how the Apostle Paul engaged with the culture and entertainment of his time. Just like Paul, we'll learn how to find God's presence even in unexpected places, whether it's in movies, music, or books. 📽️🎵📖

As we discuss this thought-provoking topic, we'll also share tips for discerning what's right for you and your family. Parents, we've got some great insights to help guide your kids through the world of media and entertainment. Join the conversation and discover how we can connect with the Gospel through the arts.

snippet.title: Your Role as a Christian in Your Family
snippet.description:
In this week's message, we're diving into how our Christian faith impacts our daily lives beyond the church walls, specifically in our families. We'll talk about how our identities shape our realities and how important it is to bring our faith into the various spheres we interact with.

Join us as we explore the importance of prioritizing faith in our families, work, and more. Don't miss this enlightening series as we discuss the intersections of faith with the world around us.

Remember, our goal is to equip you to go out and live in the new reality that Jesus has brought into our lives. If you're a Christian, we want you to feel empowered to influence the spheres you run in.

snippet.title: Why Your Life Matters: Making a Difference with Jesus
snippet.description:
Have you ever wondered if your life can make a real difference or have a desire for your life to really matter? Well, you're not alone! Today, we're talking about how we can make our lives count and share some inspiring stories along the way. 

🔥 In this video, we'll explore:

The significance of our lives and how we can leave a lasting impact.
- Jesus' final words and what they mean for us today.
- Keeping the fire burning for others to experience Jesus' love.
- We've got a powerful story about one of our amazing ministry partners and how he's spreading the gospel, even in challenging circumstances. You won't want to miss it!

snippet.title: Why should you go to church?
snippet.description:
Why should you go to church? Why is being part of a church is so important for your faith journey? Did you know that a recent study found that many people love Jesus but don't go to church? 😲 We'll explore the reasons behind this and why they might be missing out on something special.

Join us as we explore the concept of belonging and how the church can become your spiritual family. We'll share personal stories, insights, and practical reasons why being part of a church can truly enrich your life.

And remember, going to church doesn't make you a Christian - it's your faith in Jesus that counts! But we'll explain why being part of a church community can enhance your faith experience. 🙌

snippet.title: God's Grace and Why it Matters
snippet.description:
Join us for an uplifting message about God's grace and His unconditional love and why these are "Hills to Die On" when it comes to our faith. We'll also talk about the three types of grace that define our relationship with Him. 

In this video, you'll discover:

- What unconditional love means for your relationship with God.
- The three types of Grace: Prevenient, Justifying, and Sanctifying Grace.
- How Grace transforms our lives and brings us closer to God.

snippet.title: The Good Fight: Finding True Contentment
snippet.description:
In this sermon, Pastor Daniel Lumpee wraps up our four-week series called "The Good Fight" talking about finding true contentment. We've been learning from Paul's instructions to young Timothy about how to shine the light of Jesus in a dark world and fight the good fight of faith. 💪

We discovered that the weapons for this spiritual battle might not be what we expected. Instead of physical tools, Paul points to essential qualities like rejecting false teaching, the power of prayer, and living out the Gospel in our actions. Today, we focused on the weapon of "Contentment." 🛡️

Being content means finding joy and peace in what we have, rather than constantly desiring more. It's about realizing that true happiness isn't in wealth or possessions but in Jesus Christ. 

We also discussed how comparison can rob us of contentment and how having an eternal perspective helps us focus on what truly matters. And guess what? Being generous with our hearts and giving of ourselves also leads to contentment! 

So, let's remember to fix our eyes on Jesus, surrender to Him, and trust that He will make what we have enough. With Jesus on our side, we can face any challenge and fight the good fight!

snippet.title: Why Do We Worship and Why is it Important?

He challenges us to find a reason to praise God every time we walk into church, even if it is something as simple as having breath in our lungs. encourage you to find a way to worship God today. It doesn't have to be anything fancy or elaborate. Just take some time to tell God how much you love him and thank him for all he has done for you. You will be glad you did!

snippet.title: Journeying Through Acts: Faith, Perseverance, and Hope
snippet.description:
As we continue our series on Acts, we're looking at Paul's unwavering commitment to spreading the Gospel, even when faced with imprisonment and persecution. His resolve to appeal to Caesar rather than taking the easier route back to Jerusalem is a testament to his faith and dedication.

We'll also reflect on the challenges of sharing our faith, drawing inspiration from the parable of the sower in Mark 4. This parable reminds us that while not every seed we plant will grow, our efforts are never in vain. Whether the seed falls on rocky ground, among thorns, or fertile soil, our job is to continue planting and trusting God to bring the increase.

Sharing our faith can be difficult, and it's natural to feel discouraged when our efforts don't seem to bear fruit. However, we must remember that God can work through every situation. Just as the farmer in the parable doesn't give up, we too must keep sowing seeds of hope, love, and faith.

Thank you for being part of our church family. We look forward to seeing you next week as we continue to explore the incredible stories and lessons from the book of Acts.

snippet.title: Choosing Faith Over Comfort: Paul’s Journey in Acts 25
snippet.description:
In this heartfelt sermon, Thomas Lake delivers a powerful message on choosing faith over comfort. 

As he prepares for his move to Kentucky for Seminary, Thomas reflects on Paul’s unwavering faith in Acts 25. Despite the hardships Paul faced in prison, he remained committed to God’s call to go to Rome. Thomas encourages us to embrace desperation for God, like Paul and other biblical figures, to bring about true change in the world. 

Join us in this journey of faith and discover how choosing God over comfort can transform our lives and our communities.

snippet.title: Trusting God's Plan Even When We Can't See It
snippet.description:
Today we're diving into the theme of trusting in God's plan, even when we can't see it. Reflecting on Acts 23, we are reminded that God is always working for our good, orchestrating His perfect plan in our lives.

Whether you’re familiar with the story of Paul or hearing it for the first time, today’s message is a powerful reminder that God's plan for us is always better than our own. Join us in embracing this truth and finding peace in the knowledge that He is always at work, even in the unseen.

Remember, God loves you and has a wonderful plan for your life. Let’s walk this journey together, trusting in His wisdom and grace.

🙏 If you found this message encouraging, please like, share, and subscribe to our channel. God bless you!

snippet.title: The Power of Testimony | Acts 22
snippet.description:
In today’s message, we're diving into the testimony of Paul from Acts 22, exploring how his profound encounter with Jesus turned him from a persecutor of Christians to one of the greatest evangelists in history. Just as Paul's story is told multiple times in the book of Acts, emphasizing its importance, we believe that every testimony holds immense value. Your story, too, has the power to inspire and bring hope to others.

Join us as we reflect on the goodness of God and the hope we find in Jesus, even in a world that often feels hopeless. Let's be encouraged to share our own testimonies boldly, knowing that our experiences with God's grace can touch hearts and change lives.

Scripture Reference:
Acts 21-22

Prayer:
We thank you, Lord, for your presence and goodness that fills our hearts with hope. May we be emboldened to share our testimonies and spread your love. Amen.

Don't forget to like, subscribe, and hit the notification bell to stay updated with our latest messages and events. We’re so glad you’re part of our community!

snippet.title: Walking in the Spirit and Embracing God's Will
snippet.description: In today's message we're reflecting on the importance of listening to God's word repeatedly, not out of guilt but as a reminder of the guidance we constantly need. We'll revisit key lessons from previous sermons, emphasizing how walking in the Spirit and aligning ourselves with God's will are ongoing journeys. As we dive into Acts 20-21, we'll recount the story of Eutychus and Paul's unwavering determination to reach Jerusalem, despite knowing the suffering that awaited him. This powerful narrative challenges us to examine our own commitment to God's calling, even when it leads to hardships.

snippet.title: Surprised by the Spirit | Acts 20
snippet.description:
Today we're diving into Acts chapter 20, exploring the journey of the Apostle Paul and the lessons for our lives today. In today's message, Pastor Cabe dives into the story of Paul's travels and encounters in Acts 20, highlighting the importance of being open to the surprise of the Spirit in our lives. This message is not just about historical context but about how we can apply these lessons of faith and community in our modern lives.

Join us in exploring how the Spirit moves among us, awakening hearts and bringing new life!

snippet.title: Are You Living a Spirit-filled Life?
snippet.description: Are you living a Spirit-filled life or just going through the motions? Discover how the Holy Spirit can transform your daily walk with God, confront your idols, and lead you to true spiritual freedom. Learn about the significant shift from John's baptism—a symbol of repentance—to the baptism of Jesus, which beckons the Holy Spirit to initiate profound internal change. Reflect on your own spiritual practices: Are they merely weekly rituals, or do they represent a daily, devoted walk with God? snippet.title: Navigating the Journey of Faith | Guided Church
snippet.description: When we're navigating the journey of faith, it's important to have a clear guide. snippet.title: Is it truly more blessed to give than to receive?
snippet.description: Join us as Pastor Brent explores the age-old question: Is it truly more blessed to give than to receive? Discover the Greek word "Makários," meaning happy, and how living a life of generosity can lead to true happiness. Explore the correlation between the condition of our hearts and our financial choices, and how Jesus emphasized this in Matthew 6:21 and learn the scientific benefits of generosity, including increased happiness, lowered stress, improved relationships, and an extended life. Don't miss real-life stories of transformed lives through generosity and the exciting giving challenge ahead. Join us in the journey of discovering the joy and blessings that come from living a life of giving.

snippet.title: The Lord is my Shepherd: Psalm 23

snippet.title: A Joyful Christmas Celebration - Youth/Children Led Service

snippet.title: Love in Action: An Advent Reflection

snippet.title: Waiting in Hope - Advent

snippet.title: The Enduring Power of the Holy Spirit: Acts 14

snippet.title: Awakening the Spirit: Journey Through Acts

snippet.title: Living Generously
snippet.description:

We'll also dive into Acts 10 and the story of Peter's miraculous escape from prison. We'll also reflect on the impact of seeking God's will in our lives and how prayer can help us find our way even in challenging times.

So, whether you're a long-time churchgoer or new to the faith, this message is for you. Let's learn how we can live out of abundance and not scarcity, just like our generous God.

snippet.title: Is God's love for everyone? | Thomas Lake
snippet.description: Is God's love for everyone? In this video, we're diving into Acts 11 to uncover an amazing story about how God's love and power can change lives. Thomas shares a fascinating story about how Peter, one of Jesus' closest friends, had a dream that changed everything. People back then thought the good news about Jesus was only for a certain group, but Peter's dream showed that God's love is for everyone. It's like a big invitation to a party, and no one is left out! You'll be encouraged to be like Peter, to share God's love with everyone and remember that God's love can empower us to do amazing things.

snippet.title: A Journey through Acts: Peter and Cornelius

snippet.title: The Transformation of Saul - Acts 9
snippet.description:

Join us as we delve into the Book of Acts, a narration of the early church's journey, to understand the lessons it holds for us today. Just like Saul's story, this is our story too, and we can learn valuable insights from the early church's experiences.

Last week, we had our Mission Sunday, emphasizing the importance of missions in our community and around the world. Learn how you can participate in various ways - from praying for missions to making pledges for the missions offering. Join us as we uncover the power of faith and transformation.

In this passage, we witness Saul's encounter with Jesus on the road to Damascus, a life-altering moment that changed him from a persecutor to a believer. We also highlight the significance of advocacy and encouragement, exemplified by Barnabas, and how it can profoundly impact lives.

As we explore the message further, let's reflect on how we can be agents of positive change and encouragement in the lives of those around us. Join us on this spiritual journey through Acts, and may you be inspired to make a difference in your community.

snippet.title: The Journey to Awakening: Embracing the Second Half of the Gospel | JD Walt

snippet.description: In this message, we're continuing our series on Romans exploring two different ways of living —Adam's way and Jesus' way. Discover why striving to be righteous on our own, like Adam, leads to failure, while embracing the life of Christ offers a radically different perspective. These two ways of living are not parallel but opposite to each other. We'll also explore the role of the law and how love, not rule following, is the key to being in a relationship with God.

snippet.title: Romans 6: Two Paths We Can Choose
snippet.description:
Join us as we explore Romans 6 as we continue our Walk through Romans series. In this message we talk about the story of Adam and Eve, sin, and the redemption offered by Jesus. Learn about two different paths we can choose in life and how embracing God's story leads to hope and true freedom. Dive into the adventure of discovering God's love and find out how you can be a part of His incredible plan.

snippet.title: Exploring Romans 4: Discovering God's Promises
snippet.description:
Join us on a journey through the book of Romans, where we learn about the teachings of the Apostle Paul. In this chapter, Romans 4, we delve into the story of Abraham and explore the concept of righteousness through faith. We discover that Paul's writings in Romans are influenced by his encounter with Jesus, which transformed his life. By reading Romans with the lens of Jesus' grace and love, we gain a new understanding of God's promises and how they relate to our lives today.

Key Takeaways:

-Paul's letters, including Romans, were written after his encounter with Jesus, and they reflect his understanding of God's grace.
-We have an advantage as believers because we know God's promises and have access to His Word.
-Everyone, including Abraham, has sinned and fallen short of God's glory. However, through faith, we can be justified by God's grace.
-Abraham's story teaches us the importance of having hope and unwavering faith in God's promises, even when circumstances seem impossible.
-The promises made to Abraham and David in the Bible can give us confidence that God is faithful and will fulfill His promises in our lives too.
-Taking steps of faith and believing in God's power can lead to righteousness and a deeper relationship with Him.

Join us as we explore the book of Romans, uncovering God's promises, and understanding how they can impact our lives today.

snippet.title: Breakfast by the Sea
snippet.description:
As we wrap up our series, we explore Jesus' third appearance to His disciples after His resurrection. This encounter by the sea is a pivotal moment, reminding us of the significance of seeking God, no matter the time or place. Through the lens of John 21, we delve into how Jesus' simple breakfast with His disciples was more than a meal – it was a moment of restoration, reaffirmation, and a call to continue the mission He set forth.

Our sermon reflects on how we, like the disciples, may find ourselves drifting away from our spiritual commitments but are always called back by Jesus. The breakfast by the sea symbolizes a new beginning, a restoration of faith, and a reminder that Jesus never forsakes us.

snippet.title: The Miracle of the Loaves and Fish: Trusting in God’s Provision
snippet.description:
Today’s message celebrates God’s gift of another Sabbath and the miracle of Jesus feeding 5,000 people with just five loaves of bread and two fish. We explore how this story teaches us about faith, sharing, and trusting in God’s provision. This sermon highlights the importance of faith, trust, and recognizing Jesus’ sufficiency in our lives.

Join us for a heartfelt sermon, a beautiful prayer and the holy act of Communion. Let’s learn together how Jesus can do great things with even the smallest offerings.

snippet.title: Embracing Faith Amid Life's Storms
snippet.description:
Today, we continue our sermon series, "Summer by the Sea," reflecting on Jesus’ miracles and his powerful presence in our lives.

This week's message takes us back to the Sea of Galilee, where we witness Jesus walking on water, revealing his divine identity amidst a storm. Just as the disciples faced turbulent seas and found solace in Jesus, we too encounter storms in life where our faith is tested. As we navigate through these challenging times, remember that Jesus is our eternal lifeguard, ready to save us when we call out to him.

Join us as we explore the significance of having a lifeguard for our faith, the importance of reaching out to Jesus in our weakest moments, and the comfort of knowing that he is always there to rescue us from the depths of despair. Let's come together in prayer, reflection, and worship, and find strength in the presence of our Savior.

snippet.title: Jesus Calms the Storm
snippet.description:
Our ongoing sermon series, "Summer by the Sea," continues with this memorable story of Jesus calming the storm. Experience the tranquility and peace Jesus offers amidst life's sudden squalls and challenges.

In this reflection, we are reminded of God's sovereignty and love, even in the midst of trials. We learn that following Jesus doesn't exempt us from hardships, but it equips us to face them with faith and trust in His divine plan.

snippet.title: Discovering Jesus by the Sea of Galilee
snippet.description:
Today we're sharing the powerful lesson of Simon's calling by Jesus by the Sea of Galilee. We're reminded of the transformative love and grace of God, which calls us into a deeper relationship with Him.

Join us as we dive into Luke 5:1-11, exploring how Jesus' love and grace can take hold of our lives, just as it did with Simon. Let the Spirit of the Living God fall afresh on you today, melting, molding, and filling you with His presence.

May you be blessed by this message and feel God's embrace wherever you are in your faith journey. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe to our channel for more uplifting content. God bless you!

snippet.title: God's Deliverance at The Red Sea
snippet.description:
In this powerful message, we'll explore the miraculous parting of the Red Sea, a story not just of ancient history but one that continues to hold deep significance for us today. We'll reflect on how God's mighty acts of deliverance can inspire and guide us through the 'Red Seas' in our own lives – those seemingly insurmountable obstacles that we face.

🔍 Sermon Highlights:

- Understanding the historical and spiritual importance of the Red Sea event.
- How God's deliverance then mirrors His ability to rescue us from our own challenges today.
- Insights from modern science that affirm the possibility of this miraculous event.
- The ultimate power of faith and the presence of God in our lives.

Let’s gather together, whether in the sanctuary or online from around the world, to find encouragement and strength in God's word. Stand firm, be still, and witness the deliverance of the Lord.

snippet.title: Independence or Dependence?
snippet.description: Bishop Hayes concludes our powerful sermon series, "Faith Grows Here," with an inspiring message that ties together faith, patriotism, and the teachings of Jesus. Through the imagery of plants and nature, we explore how our faith can flourish when we trust in God, just as our nation has done throughout its history. Let us come together in prayer and gratitude, celebrating the divine providence that continues to guide and sustain us. As we gather to worship, may this service plant seeds of faith, hope, and unity in our hearts, reminding us of God's unwavering presence in our lives and our nation.

snippet.title: Jesus is the True Vine
snippet.description: Explore the profound spiritual truths of Jesus as the 'true vine' in John 15, where he teaches the importance of abiding in him to bear spiritual fruit. This connection is vital because, apart from Jesus, we can do nothing. By remaining in Christ, we produce the fruits of the Spirit, with love being the most significant evidence of a life intertwined with Jesus. Reflect on your relationship with Jesus and how it manifests in your daily life, ensuring that your faith journey is one of active engagement and abundant fruitfulness.

snippet.title: Moses: A Journey Beyond Doubt
snippet.description: Dive into the story of Moses and the burning bush with our latest video, where we uncover the essence of faith and our response to God's call. This biblical narrative is not just a tale from the past but a guiding light for our spiritual journey, inviting us to consider the nature of our own faith. Discover the significance of removing barriers to connect with the divine, the relational nature of God, and the importance of trusting in His vision for our lives. Learn about the sacred calling of 'I AM' and how to live a life fully committed to God. Join us as we explore the meaning of standing on holy ground and embracing our calling within God's divine plan. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe for more enriching content!

snippet.title: The Power of Mustard Seed Faith
snippet.description: Ever considered the power of a tiny seed? 🌱 This message emphasizes the beauty of small beginnings and how your mustard seed faith can grow into something extraordinary. In this message we explore the beauty of small beginnings and highlight the transformative power of God, who makes everything beautiful in its time. The parable of the mustard seed illustrates that the kingdom of God often starts small, and we are encouraged to take tangible steps to nurture our faith, like daily scripture reading and prayer, recognizing that even the smallest acts can have a significant impact in God's kingdom.

snippet.title: The Parable of the Sower
snippet.description: What kind of soil is your heart? In this message we're exploring the profound lessons of the Parable of the Sower, where Jesus teaches about the conditions of the human heart through the metaphor of soil. Discover how the seed, representing God's word, fares differently on the path of the hard heart, the rocky ground of the shallow heart, among the thorns of the crowded heart, and in the good soil of the fruitful heart. This message will challenge you to reflect on your own spiritual receptivity and consider how to cultivate a heart that embraces and bears the fruits of God's message.

Discover the keys to spiritual growth and how to cultivate a life that bears fruit in every season. Learn how to deepen your roots in God's word and trust in His plan for you. This sermon is a must-watch for anyone seeking to grow in faith and understanding. Don't forget to subscribe for more inspiring messages.

Understand the true meaning of God's grace and how the Holy Spirit's empowerment transformed ordinary disciples into bold apostles. Learn the importance of waiting on God and inviting the Holy Spirit into your life. This sermon is a must-watch for anyone seeking spiritual growth, empowerment, and a deeper relationship with God. snippet.title: Understanding God's Grace Through Sacrificial Living
snippet.description: Discover the transformative power of God's grace in our latest message, 'Understanding God's Grace Through Sacrificial Living'. Dive into the biblical story of Ruth and Naomi and learn how 'hesed', the Hebrew concept of loving kindness, is demonstrated through their lives. This sermon unpacks the importance of living sacrificially as a reflection of God's grace and how it leads to an abundant life in Christ. Don't miss out on understanding how everyday acts of obedience can have an extraordinary impact.

snippet.title: The Power of Grace
snippet.description:
Discover the power of transformative grace in this enlightening sermon drawing from Psalm 100 and the life-changing experience of the Apostle Paul on the road to Damascus. Join us as we dive into the story of Saul's transformation into Paul and consider how God's grace might be calling you to a new path. This sermon explores the joy of worship, the importance of thankfulness, and the various types of grace that influence our spiritual journey. Whether you're seeking inspiration, looking to deepen your faith, or curious about the impact of God's grace, this sermon offers valuable insights into how God's love can dramatically alter our lives.  Don't forget to like, subscribe, and share this video with those who might find hope and encouragement in its message.

snippet.description:
In this message we'll dive into the story of Esther and learn the importance of recognizing your royal identity in Christ, exercising your God-given authority, and interceding for others in times of crisis. Discover how Esther's courageous actions to save her people exemplify the Christian calling to partner with God through prayer and action. This message will inspire you to embrace your calling "for such a time as this" and to live out your faith with boldness and conviction. Don't miss this transformative message that will challenge you to step into your spiritual authority and make a difference in the world. snippet.description:
Living a life filled with grace also means embracing God's sovereignty. Dive into the biblical story of Joseph and learn how God's grace can turn trials into triumphs. This message will challenge you to see God's hand in every aspect of your life and to trust in His sovereignty. Whether you're facing adversity or celebrating success, this sermon will encourage you to live a grace-filled life. Don't miss this powerful exploration of faith, forgiveness, and divine purpose.

Discover the profound message of grace and redemption as we share about the poignant encounter between Jesus and Peter, where forgiveness and duty intertwine. snippet.title: Journey to the Upper Room | Maundy Thursday 2024
snippet.description: Join us as we experience the transformative events of the Last Supper. We'll journey to the Upper Room, experiencing the profound moments where Jesus initiated the Eucharist, gave the new commandment of love, and humbly washed his disciples' feet. Through powerful readings from Exodus, Psalms, Luke, and John, witness the fulfillment of ancient prophecies and the establishment of the New Covenant. Our service invites you to immerse yourself in the spiritual significance of this sacred occasion, reflecting on its eternal message of redemption and sacrificial love.

snippet.title: Where is Jesus? | Easter 2024
snippet.description:
Today, we're we're reflecting on the timeless message of Easter Sunday. Discover how the story of Mary's encounter with the risen Jesus prompts us to ask the profound question, "Where is Jesus?" Explore the relevance of this question in our lives today, especially in times of uncertainty, grief, and despair. Through insightful anecdotes and powerful storytelling, we learn how believing in the resurrection transforms our perspective on life's challenges.

Join us as we bridge the gap between merely celebrating Easter and truly believing in its life-changing power. Explore how embracing the resurrection message empowers us to navigate life's trials with unwavering faith and hope. Experience the profound truth that Jesus is not confined to the pages of history but is actively present in our lives, seeking to bring us comfort, renewal, and redemption.

Don't miss out on this enlightening discussion that will deepen your understanding of Easter and inspire you to live with renewed faith and purpose. Subscribe now and join our community as we journey together in faith, hope, and love.

snippet.title: Good Friday 2024
snippet.description: In this video, we dissect the intense emotions and pivotal events surrounding the Passover table, the Garden of Gethsemane, and the crucifixion, as depicted in the Gospel narratives. Join us as we explore the disciples' turmoil, the agony of Jesus in the garden, and the profound statements uttered from the cross. Through poignant prayers, solemn reflections, and heartfelt worship, we invite you to journey with us into the heart of Good Friday, pondering its relevance for our lives today. Experience the power of forgiveness, the depths of Jesus' love, and the transformative impact of his sacrifice as we pause, remember, and contemplate the profound mysteries of this sacred day.

snippet.title: Embracing Joy and Sorrow
snippet.description: Today we're talking about the bittersweet nature of life and faith in this moving sermon, reflecting on Jesus' emotional journey during Holy Week. As you watch, you'll learn about the importance of embracing both joy and sorrow, seeking solace in God, and the value of community support through grief. This sermon will inspire you to open your heart to Jesus to find the peace he offers, avoiding the regret of "if only." Whether you're experiencing grief or searching for deeper meaning, this message is for you. Join us in exploring the transformative power of Jesus' love and the hope of eternal life. Don't forget to subscribe for more uplifting sermons and spiritual guidance.

snippet.title: Rest and Renewal
snippet.description: In this message, we'll discuss the importance of rest and renewal during the Lenten season, drawing from the Gospel of Mark and the story of Jesus inviting his disciples to rest. We'll share about the need for spiritual rest and the biblical perspective on the Sabbath, highlighting how Jesus offers a deeper rest than the law could provide. The message also touches on modern society's struggle with rest and the various methods people use to achieve it, ultimately pointing to Jesus as the ultimate source of rest for the weary. Discover how unplugging from the world and surrendering to God's grace can lead to profound spiritual healing and inner peace.

snippet.title: How do we prepare for life's challenges?
snippet.description:
How do we prepare for life's challenges? This message will encourage you to explore the theme of preparation, both in Jesus' ministry and in your own life. Reflect on the importance of being equipped for life's challenges and embracing disappointments as avenues for divine blessings. As we journey through Lent, let's prepare our hearts to embrace the fullness of life promised by God.

Join us as we uncover lessons from Jesus' prayerful preparation as he approached the cross. We'll look at how Jesus, despite knowing his impending death, sought solace in communion with his Father. Discover the pivotal moment when Jesus challenges his disciples with the question: "Who do you say I am?" and the significance of Peter's declaration.

snippet.title: The Significance of Lent
snippet.description: Join us as we journey into the sacred journey of Lent, exploring the depths of reflection, prayer, and spiritual renewal. In today's message, Pastor Margarita reflects on the significance of Lent from her childhood memories to the profound understanding she gained through faith in Jesus and seminary education. She unpacks the scripture passage from Luke 5, highlighting Jesus' compassionate touch and intentional prayer life and shares practical insights that invite viewers to join in a deeper communion with God.

snippet.title: [Full Service] Finding God in the Quiet Places: Prayer
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | March 3, 2024 | Rev. Margarita McCarthy

The season of Lent has its roots in the 40 days Jesus spent fasting and being tempted in the wilderness. Just as Christ relied on the Word of God to sustain Him, we, too, must use this season to nourish our souls as we experience our own temptations. One way for us to prepare ourselves and be ready for the great festival of the resurrection of Christ, which Easter celebrates, is to find God in the quiet places along our own Lenten journey. The prophet Isaiah wrote, “Seek the Lord while he may be found; call upon him while he is near.” In this holy, 40-day season, our sermon series is designed to help us seek and find God in the tranquil and peaceful places where we, like Christ, can be victorious over all those things that separate us from God. We are delighted you have joined us for our Lenten journey.

snippet.title: Connect with God in the Quiet Places
snippet.description: In this message, we explore the theme of finding God in the quiet places, reflecting on the importance of wisdom and discernment in our daily lives. We'll uncover the significance of carving out moments of communion with God amidst the busyness of life. Discover how Jesus himself sought clarity and strength through prayer in quiet moments, and how we can emulate his example to find direction and empowerment in our own journeys of faith. Join us as we learn practical ways to eliminate hurry and cultivate a deeper connection with God, leading to a life filled with spiritual growth, clarity, and power.

snippet.title: Finding God in Quiet Places: Solitude
snippet.description: As we begin the season of Lent, we are exploring solitude and how we can find God in quiet places. Journey with us through biblical teachings, reflecting on Jesus' retreats to lonely places and the restoration of souls. Discover how the season of Lent beckons us to reconnect with the essence of our being, nurturing our souls in the embrace of divine love. This message will help you grasp the significance of stillness amidst life's chaos and the devil's temptation to drown us in noise. Learn to embrace the wilderness of the soul, where fears dissolve in the gentle whisper of God's presence.

snippet.title: Blueprint for Living: The Beatitudes
snippet.description: Today we're exploring the timeless wisdom of the Beatitudes in our series, "Blueprint for Living." In this message we'll talk about the profound teachings of Jesus from the Sermon on the Mount, uncovering the keys to living a truly blessed life amidst the challenges of the world. Join us as we decode each beatitude, contrasting it with the world's standards, and discover how to cultivate a life of spiritual richness, peace, and fulfillment. Don't miss out on this transformative journey towards understanding the essence of true happiness and fulfillment.

snippet.title: Building a Solid Life
snippet.description: Today we're talking about building a solid life using the timeless "blueprint" God gives us in His word. In this powerful message, discover the secrets of a strong foundation, drawing parallels between life's challenges and the construction of a sturdy structure. Sometimes life feels like a roller coaster but we can navigate the ups and downs with resilience and purpose. Learn from the insightful analogy of building on rock versus sand, and uncover the timeless teachings found in Matthew's gospel, chapter 7. Join us on this profound exploration of faith, wisdom, and the timeless blueprint that guides us in living a life built on Christ, the solid rock.

snippet.title: Extraordinary Devotion: Growing in Grace
snippet.description:
In this message, Pastor Karen explores the theme of "Extraordinary Devotion" and discusses what it means to be a growing church in the grace of Jesus Christ.

🌟 Highlights:
- Discover the significance of devotion to God's word, fellowship, breaking bread, and prayer in a growing church.
- Learn how ordinary people, when encountering an extraordinary God, can impact their communities.
- Explore the compassionate and caring nature of a growing church, making a positive difference in the lives of others.
- Celebrate the gift of Jesus Christ and the transformative power of gratitude.

snippet.title: Being a Grateful Church
snippet.description: This week we're talking about being a grateful church as we explore the theme of gratitude in stewardship. Discover how, like Zacchaeus, we can experience a transformative encounter with Jesus, leading to a profound shift in our perspectives and actions. Be inspired to embrace a life of gratitude and generosity. Watch, reflect, and consider your own spiritual journey as we embark on this third week of our stewardship campaign.

snippet.title: Navigating Life's Challenges with Jesus as Our Compass
snippet.description:
In the midst of life's challenges, Jesus is our compass. In today's message, we're exploring the concept of being a guided church, drawing inspiration from the timeless teachings of Jesus. Discover the importance of having a clear direction and keeping the main thing, Jesus, at the center of your life. We'll talk about how being a guided church means ministering to the world, meeting community needs, and following the path that Jesus modeled for us. Be inspired to invest your deepest treasures in heavenly pursuits and find your way home, guided by the unchanging symbol of our faith – the cross. Don't miss this transformative message that encourages us to navigate life's challenges with Jesus as our unwavering compass. 

#GuidedChurch #Sermon2024 #JesusAsCompass

snippet.title: Generosity and the Church
snippet.description: Join us as we reflect on the church's DNA of generosity, and look at how it defines the church and shapes its identity. Whether you're attending in person at Woodlands Methodist Church or joining us online from anywhere in the world, this message invites you to consider the seven forms of generosity and the joyous blessings it brings, both to givers and recipients.

snippet.title: Embracing Unmet Expectations with Hope
snippet.description: Life is full of unmet expectations, but how can we embrace these unmet expectations with hope? As we transition into the new year, let's be encouraged to recognize unmet expectations and find hope in the Christmas season, emphasizing the importance of clinging to God's will for our future. Experience the joy of surrendering to the movement of the Holy Spirit as we enter 2024 with renewed faith and purpose.

snippet.title: The Cast of Christmas: Behind the Scenes of the Greatest Story Ever Told
snippet.description:
In this special Christmas sermon, we'll explore the behind-the-scenes moments that led to the birth of Jesus and discuss the timeless significance of this extraordinary event. Share in the wonder and beauty of the Christmas story as we reflect on the characters who, though often overlooked, played crucial roles in God's divine plan. Be prepared to be inspired and reawakened to the joy of Christmas!
As we approach Christmas 2023, let's become the extras in God's story, living out the Christmas message of love, kindness, and joy every day.

snippet.title: Preparing for the King: The Wonder of Advent
snippet.description: Join Pastor Drew Essen as he explores the theme of preparation during the Advent season. Discover the true motivation behind your holiday preparations as we continue our series, The Wonder of it All. From personal reflections to the biblical story of John the Baptist, learn how to prepare your heart with joy, peace, and hope for the coming of the King. Don't miss this insightful message that encourages us to go beyond the surface of the holiday rush and embrace the deeper meaning of Christmas.

snippet.title: God's Promises of Love and Salvation
snippet.description: As we continue to explore the promises God made throughout history, leading us to the birth of Jesus, we focus on Isaiah's prophecy and the assurance of a Messiah who brings love and salvation. In this message, Bishop Hayes reflects on the timeless promise of a Messiah, tracing God's plan through the Old Testament prophets to the birth of Jesus. Learn how God's promises are not only declarations but tangible expressions of His love and the gift of salvation.

snippet.title: The Wonder of It All: The Prophecy
snippet.description:
There is an unexplainable mystery that proclaims the seasons of Advent and Christmas, a story so steeped in simplicity and awe that it transcends everything we thought we knew about the God we serve. Mankind has always sought God in many unusual ways, but the Christmas story is about God
pursuing us, and on the night a child was born in the city of Bethlehem, God found us. Since then, our world has not been the same. Prophets, angels, shepherds and wise men heralded the good news,
and their message declared the greatest wonder of all: “Emmanuel — God is with us!” It is a story that never grows old, and we are delighted you are here to experience Advent and Christmas once again and to celebrate The Wonder of It All.

snippet.title: Gratitude in the Storm: Finding Blessings Amidst Life's Challenges
snippet.description:
How do we find gratitude in the midst of life's storms? Join us for a message of hope, gratitude, and faith as we explore the importance of maintaining a posture of gratitude, even when faced with the unpredictable storms of life.

🙏 Pastor Mark Sorensen leads us through a powerful reflection on the story of Jesus and the ten lepers, illustrating how gratitude can bring healing and wholeness. Whether you're facing challenges, uncertainties, or simply seeking inspiration, this message is for you.

snippet.title: Overcoming Evil with Good
snippet.description:
Join us as we delve into the current sermon series, "Storm Warnings," with a focus on the red flag alert to the storm of evil. Learn how, as Christians, we can navigate through the challenges of life and stand strong against the winds of evil.

Join us on this journey of faith as we strive to live out our calling to be lights in a world that sometimes seems dark. Share this video with friends and family, and let's encourage one another to stand firm in the face of adversity.

snippet.title: All Saints Sunday: Weathering Life's Storms and Celebrating Loved Ones
snippet.description:
Welcome to our All Saints Sunday service at The Woodlands Methodist Church. Today, we have a heartfelt message for you. We'll be exploring the significance of this special day when we remember our loved ones who have passed away and celebrate the eternal connection we share with them.

In this video, you'll find comfort, inspiration, and a profound message of hope as we navigate the storms of life, including the ultimate challenge—death. Join us as we honor and remember those who have gone ahead of us and are now in God's presence, watching over us.

We'll also delve into the powerful words of the Apostle Paul, who, even from his prison cell, left us with an enduring legacy of faith and perseverance. Discover the true meaning of finishing the race and keeping the faith.

Don't miss this uplifting message that reminds us that, with God, we can weather any storm and celebrate the lives of those who have received their heavenly crown. If you're looking for guidance, comfort, and spiritual insight, this video is for you.

snippet.title: How do we resist temptation?
snippet.description:
How do we resist temptation in the middle of life's storms? In this message we'll explore the biblical wisdom that helps us stay strong when temptations come knocking. We'll also discover the valuable lessons from the temptations Jesus faced in the wilderness.

Join us as we dive into the power of God's Word and find out how it can be our anchor in the stormy sea of life. Remember, you're not alone in this journey – we're here with you every step of the way.

snippet.title: Storm Warnings: Finding Hope in the Midst of Fear
snippet.description:
In this message, we're talking about fear and about how you can find hope in the midst of fear. We'll explore the story from the Book of Acts, where a group of people faced a terrifying storm and how they found hope and guidance. We'll talk about dealing with fear and doubt and discover how God sends help in unexpected ways.

Remember, even in the most challenging moments, God is with us, providing support and direction. When you're in the middle of a storm, don't forget to look around and see who God has placed in your path to help you through.

Join us on this spiritual journey as we learn to weather life's storms and emerge stronger on the other side. Don't forget to like, subscribe, and share this message with your friends and family.

snippet.title: The Power of Sharing Jesus: Making a Difference in the World
snippet.description:
In today's message, we explore the profound impact we can make by sharing the love of Jesus with the world. Join us as we discuss the importance of reaching out to others and spreading the Gospel, reflecting on our mission to make a difference and bring hope to those in need. Discover how we can all play a part in this beautiful journey of faith and love.

Join us for this inspiring sermon and be motivated to be a part of something bigger than yourself. Let's make a lasting difference in the lives of those around us!

snippet.title: When God says No, His Grace says Yes
snippet.description:
In this sermon, we reflect on how even when God says no, His grace always says yes. We learn from the story of Moses, a revered figure in the Old Testament, who, despite his close relationship with God, was denied entry into the Promised Land. Explore the reasons behind God's decision and the valuable lessons we can apply in our own lives.

👉 Key Takeaways:

- Breaking faith with God.
- Recognizing God's power and glory.
- The importance of humility in our journey.
God's blessings vs. our self-reliance.
Join us as we uncover the profound message of faith, humility, and God's incredible grace that applies to us today.

snippet.title: Take This Cup From Me: When God Says No
snippet.description:
Our current sermon series, “When God Says No,” continues this week as we are taken to the Garden of Gethsemane to hear Jesus’ words of agony: “Take this cup from me.” 

What is the cup that Jesus refers to, and why would He make such a request of His Heavenly Father? But what is even more puzzling is why would God not grant permission in the final hours of His only Son’s life? These are the questions that we will address in this message - the answers might surprise you! Join us as we reflect on the significance of Jesus' sacrifice and learn to understand what it means when God says no to our requests.

snippet.title: When God Says No: Understanding God's Response
snippet.description:
Have you ever wondered why God sometimes says "no" to our prayers? You're not alone! In this series, we'll uncover the wisdom behind God's responses to our petitions.

In today's message, we explore the powerful story of the Apostle Paul and how he responded when God denied his request. It's a message of hope, humility, and discovering God's amazing grace in our trials.

#prayer #whengodsaysno #answeredprayers #unansweredprayers

snippet.title: Unity in the Church: Lessons from Romans
snippet.description:
Join us as we explore the powerful message of unity and faith in today's sermon. In this message, we'll discuss the lessons we can learn from the book of Romans and how they apply to our lives as followers of Jesus.

📖 Today's Scripture Reading: Romans 15:1-7

In this sermon, we'll dive into:

✝️ The importance of unity in the church
✝️ Overcoming divisions and finding common ground
✝️ Serving God in harmony, despite our differences
✝️ Embracing God's love and grace in our daily lives

Whether you're a long-time member of our congregation or a first-time visitor, we hope this message will inspire and uplift you. Let's come together as a church family and learn how to live out our faith in unity.

🙏 If you enjoy this sermon, please like, share, and subscribe to our channel for more inspirational messages and worship services. Don't forget to hit the notification bell so you never miss an update!

#unity #faith #unityinthechurch #romans

snippet.description:
Join us as we dive into the Word and discover how God's will may require a sacrifice from us. Learn how to put on Christ, take up your cross, and lay aside the works of darkness as we explore Romans 12 and 13. Let's live a life of love and sacrifice that brings renewal to our hearts and hope to the world.

Enjoy this message? Don't forget to hit that like button, subscribe, and share this message with your friends and family.

snippet.description:
Join us as we unravel the mystery of God's master plan in the book of Romans chapters 9-11. We're here to learn, grow, and find our way through life's challenges together.

In today's message:
🌿 Learn how God orchestrates His divine plan through history.
🌟 Discover the importance of being grafted into God's family.
🕯️ Be inspired to be the light for the coming generation.

Join our church family as we explore the wisdom of Romans together 🙌  and don't forget to hit that thumbs-up button, subscribe, and ring the notification bell to stay updated with our messages every week.

snippet.title: The Problem and the Cure: How We Find Forgiveness and Transformation in Christ
snippet.description:
Today, we're diving into the powerful message about "The Problem and the Cure." We'll explore how we find forgiveness for our sins and become more like Christ. It's an exciting journey through the Book of Romans that you won't want to miss!

In this video, you'll discover:

- What Paul's letter to the Romans teaches us about our relationship with God.
- How sin affects our lives and why we need Jesus.
- The amazing gift of salvation through Christ's sacrifice.
- How the Holy Spirit helps us become better people.

Join us in this spiritual adventure and learn how you can be transformed by God's love and grace. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe for more inspiring messages from our church!

#forgiveness #transformation #onlinechurch #bookofromans

snippet.title: Faith, Hope, and God's Love: A Journey Through Romans
snippet.description:
Today, we continue our series, "Survival of the Fittest," where we explore the Book of Romans, digging into faith, righteousness, and what it means to be spiritually fit. Last week, we talked about righteous judgment. This week, we'll delve deeper into faith, a crucial aspect of our spiritual journey.

But here's a little story for you! While Bishop Hayes was preparing this sermon, he stumbled upon a hidden treasure - a clay coaster with a profound quote: "Faith is to believe what you do not yet see; the reward for faith is to see what you believe." 🙌✨ Talk about a God moment!

So, what does faith mean to you? How large is your faith? 🤔 Today, we'll explore these questions and dive into the incredible faith journey of Abraham, as explained by the Apostle Paul in Romans.

As we go through this message, remember that faith isn't just about believing in Jesus; it's about trusting in His promises, even in the face of adversity. When we embrace suffering and affirm the resurrection, our faith expands, making us more like Christ.

So, join us as we explore faith, hope, and God's incredible love in today's sermon. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe to our channel for more inspiring content. 

🔔 Stay tuned for more uplifting messages and worship services! God bless you all. 🙏

#romans #survivalofthefittest #faith #faithhopeandlove
